All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    AccountResponse
    AccountResponse represents a response to the frontend with a User's account information.
    Address
    The Address class is incomplete, as it is not currently being utilized by this software product.
    AddressRepository
    This repository is incomplete.
    AddToCartRequest
    AddToCartRequest represents a request from the frontend to add some quantity of a Product to a User's cart.
    AuthController
    AuthController manages authentication requests from the frontend.
    AuthEntryPointJwt
    AuthEntryPointJwt is responsible for catching errors during the authentication process in AuthTokenFilter.
    AuthTokenFilter
    AuthTokenFilter is executed once per each HTTP request made to the server.
    BackendApplication
    BackendApplication is the starting point of this backend application.
    Category
    A Category represents a family of Products.
    CategoryController
    CategoryController manages requests from the frontend related to Category objects.
    CategoryListRequest
    CategoryListRequest represents a request from the frontend for a list of Category objects from a list of category IDs.
    CategoryRepository
    CategoryRepository manages access to the MongoDB related to Categories.
    CheckoutRequest
    CheckoutRequest represents a request from the frontend for a User to begin the checkout process.
    CustomAccessDeniedHandler
    CustomAccessDeniedHandler processes the errors that were flagged in AuthEntryPointJwt.
    DataInitializer
    DataInitializer provides basic roles and an admin user to newly created backend applications.
    ERole
    ERole is an enum containing the available User roles.
    JwtResponse
    JwtResponse represents a response to the frontend with a JWT token after a User has just logged in.
    JwtUtils
    JwtUtils is a utility class that provides methods for working with JSON Web Tokens (JWT).
    LoginRequest
    LoginRequest represents a request from the frontend for a User login token.
    LogoutRequest
    LogoutRequest represents a request from the frontend for a User to be logged out.
    MessageResponse
    MessageResponse represents a generic String response to the frontend.
    Order
    Order contains details of an order places by a User.
    OrderController
    This class is incomplete.
    OrderRepository
    OrderRepository manages access to the MongoDB related to Orders.
    OrderResponse
    OrderResponse represents a response to the frontend with Order details for a User after the user has placed the order.
    PlaceOrderRequest
    PlaceOrderRequest represents a request from the frontend for a User to place an Order after starting the checkout process and receiving a PreOrder.
    PreOrder
    A PreOrder provides a User with the details of their order before the order is confirmed and paid for.
    PreOrderRepository
    PreOrderRepository manages access to the MongoDB related to PreOrders.
    PreOrderResponse
    PreOrderResponse represents a response to the frontend with PreOrder details that the User must confirm before placing their order.
    Product
    Product represents a commercial product to be sold in the online marketplace.
    ProductController
    ProductController manages requests from the frontend related to Products.
    ProductListRequest
    ProductListRequest represents a request from the frontend for a list of Product objects from a list of Product IDs.
    ProductRepository
    ProductRepository manages access to the MongoDB related to Products.
    ProfileResponse
    ProfileResponse represents a response to the frontend with profile details for a User.
    Role
    Role represents a User's role as it pertains to authorization and access to backend mappings.
    RoleRepository
    RoleRepository manages access to the MongoDB related to Roles.
    SignupRequest
    SignupRequest represents a request from the frontend to sign up a new User with the given username, email, Roles, and password.
    Token
    Token is used only for whitelisting JWT tokens.
    TokenWhitelist
    TokenWhitelist manages access to the MongoDB related to Tokens.
    TokenWhitelistService
    TokenWhitelistService provides PreAuthorize functionality to http request controllers such as UserController.
    User
    A User represents Customers, Employees, and Admins for this marketplace.
    UserController
    UserController manages requests from the frontend related to Users.
    UserDetailsImpl
    UserDetailsImpl contains the required information to build an Authentication object.
    UserDetailsServiceImpl
    UserDetailsServiceImpl is used to build UserDetailsImpl objects.
    UserRepository
    UserRepository manages access to the MongoDB related to Users.
    WebSecurityConfig
    WebSecurityConfig provides HttpSecurity configurations for this app.
